(fifthQuint)Neurally Adjusted Ventilatory Assist (NAVA) in Pediatric Patients.

 Asynchrony means that the timing of support given by ventilator is different from patients own breathing pattern.

 Asynchrony during ventilatory care may increase the risk for complications, make the weaning more difficult and may affect the survival rates.

 In our study we randomly treat pediatric patients needing ventilatory support with neurally adjusted ventilatory assist and pressure controlled or PRVC-ventilation.

 We are willing to find out if there are any special benefits for patients with each treatment mode.

